reviewText:
Pure joy!

1/2 star for Gabriel Pimental
+1/2 star for Joe Gnoffo
+1/2 star for Dana Michael Woods
+1/2 star for Bradley Laise
+1 star for Chris' dreams of clown school
+1 star for Susan looking 20-25 years older than her husband with whom she has a 17 year old son
+1 star for Valerio Zanoli's imdb page, especially the trivia section
-3 stars for Dennis Rodman's acting not improving in his 14 year acting career
+3 stars for the BEST MUSIC EVER PUT TO FILM!!!!
Released some years ago as The Minis. Dwarf actors Joey Gnoffo and Gabriel Pimentel enlist Rodman to join their team in a charity game. It was okay.
I'm a big fan of Dennis Rodman.  Yet I still couldn't last more than 10 minutes.
